message.text:
■□■お誕生日おめでとう、国際交流基金！■□■
■□■Happy Birthday, The Japan Foundation!!!■□■

10月1日は国際交流基金が独立行政法人として再出発した記念日、明日10月2日は、国際交流基金が生まれた誕生日です！

これからも、世界の皆さんに日本のことばや文化を知ってもらうため、そして皆さんと私たちとの友情がより一層深まることを願って、様々なイベントやプログラムをお届けしていきます:)
これからもよろしくお願いします！

Today, October 1st and tomorrow, 2nd are the special dates for the Japan Foundation(JF)！
Oct.1 is the anniversary that JF was reorganized as an independent administrative institution in 2003, and on Oct.2 of 1972, JF was established.

The Japan Foundation will continue delivering various events and projects to you all around the world to share fun experiences of Japanese language and Japanese culture, as well as to deepen our friendship between you and us:)
Stay Tuned!!!

message.text:
Brazil: Oct 11-12 Exhibition "Washi-e" 
Take a look at these beautiful Japanese Autumn scenery!
ブラジル：10/11-12 展示　和紙絵
http://fjsp.org.br/agenda/washie2014/

"Washi"（わし、和紙）is a type of Japanese paper made by hand in the traditional manner. Because of its manufacturing manner, Washi is consisted of long fibers, which makes it so strong and it is even said that it lasts a thousand year!

Not only for the documents nor artworks, Washi is also used for Japanese architectural purposes.Since Washi is easy for temperature and humid control, we often use Washi for sliding doors, screens, lanterns and so on.

You can find Washi everywhere in Japan :)

message.text:
#Hiragana Master
Say it Together! Basic Japanese Words in Japanese Alphabetical Order.
Today's Word is "Ne" NERU（to sleep)　#nihongo　
日本の単語を五十音順にわかりやすく紹介！「ね」る
 
As we spend one-forth of our lifetime on sleeping (Neru-koto, ねる こと), it is absolutely imperative for us.

A Chinese proverb says that "In Spring one sleeps a sleep that knows no dawn (春眠暁を覚えず、しゅんみん あかつきを おぼえず)" , a popular saying in Japan as well, meaning that spring brings a warm breeze and moderate weather which makes people sleepy.

Like Spring, we have some typical expressions for each season. As for Autumn, it is an "eating season" (食欲の秋、しょくよく の あき) because we have various seasonal food around this season; grapes, pumpkins, chestnuts, and so on!!

Also, people enjoy sports and books in Autumn, which adds more expressions to this season, “スポーツの秋(すぽーつ の あき)”, ”読書の秋(どくしょ の あき).”

In Japan, you can immerse in the four diverse seasons（四季、しき） and enjoy the diversity in our culture! 

春には「春眠暁を覚えず」とはよく言いますが、秋に良く聞く表現は何でしょうか？
やはり旬な食材がたくさん・・・ということで、今年も食欲の秋がやってきます！
その他にも、「スポーツの秋」や「読書の秋」など、日本では昔から、気候だけでなく文化や風習も合わせて季節を楽しんでいます！

http://words.marugotoweb.jp/search_detail.php?id=1852,739&p=1&q=ねます&source=search&lang=en
